This is the "old man bar" to end all "old men bars. The bartender is a very sweet woman, the people are a mix of barflies who have been coming here since 1974 (the place probably looked exactly the same back then) and people from across the neighborhood from Chinatown to the Latin side. There's sports on the TV and Freddy Fender on a Wurlitzer jukebox that is even more beautiful because someone kicked one of the speakers in. We'll see you there next time, hiding in a corner.
